column5: I've got a chance to go to Canada next June with my neighbor. It's a lodge on Cygnet lake near Minaki. How is the fishing? I usually fish at Caviar Lake and just north of Sioux Narrows on LOTW, How do the 2 areas compare? Thanks.

I don't think Cygnet Lake is a part of the Winnipeg River system that would be referrred to as "Minaki", but I could be wrong. The fishing on the Winnipeg River can be really good that time of year for all species. What species are you fishing for?
Two guys I fish with have been going to Cygnet for 20 years. Email Bob at [email protected] or Tom at [email protected]. They can give you some info.

I have stayed there many time nice place but I went to Winnipeg River to fish muskies. I camped there but I see that the new owners have updated cabins and added new ones. It has been about 10 years since I stayed there but I go by it every year when Im up there deer hunting. The lake is great for smalles notherns and walleyes, lake is good size with many bays. Brian
